Function: conjvec
Section: conversions
C-Name: conjvec
Prototype: Gp
Help: conjvec(x): conjugate vector of the algebraic number x
Doc: 
 conjugate vector representation of $x$. If $x$ is a
 polmod, equal to \kbd{Mod}$(a,T)$, this gives a vector of length
 $\text{degree}(T)$ containing:
 
 \item the complex embeddings of $x$ if $T$ has rational coefficients, 
 i.e.~the $a(r[i])$ where $r = \kbd{polroots}(T)$;
 
 \item the lifted conjugates of $x$ if $T$ has some intmod coefficients;
 i.e.~the $x^{p^i}$ lifted to $\Z[t].
 
 \noindent If $x$ is an integer or a rational number, the result is~$x$. If
 $x$ is a (row or column) vector, the result is a matrix whose columns are
 the conjugate vectors of the individual elements of $x$.
